HEADWORD: Emaculate
<hw>E*mac"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>emaculatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>emaculare</ets> to clear from
spots. See <er>Maculate</er>.]</ety> <def>To clear from spots or stains,
or from any imperfection.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hales.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

